race.comment: Keen on SABAJ (8) to round out a big day. He's a lightly raced gelding who was kept very safe in the market first up in the G3 Silver Eagle behind Linebacker, solid there when beaten 3.5 lengths. Last preparation he measured up well against some good horses and he should strip fitter second up in what looks a very winnable race. Zahra hops aboard from the ideal gate and he gets in very well at the weights. SUNSHINEINMYPOCKET (7) and NDOLA (3) come through a good BM84 at Caulfield last time out. SUNSHINEINMYPOCKET started $2.60 there and just got held up a touch as NDOLA went for home. Doubt there's much between them but the former can certainly turn the tables. PERSIAN SPIRIT (12) has come back very well. He was unsuited staying at 1200m last time, now up in trip he can improve. HE'LL RIP (14) is racing well and did win impressively over this route two back.
